    "When accounting for Bonferroni correction, no significant differences were observed for scores of Reader 1, although a slight trend of higher scores towards the interpolated images was observed.",
    "Reader 2 scored higher signal-to-noise ratio, anatomical conspicuity, image quality, and diagnostic confidence for the baseline model compared to interpolation.",
    "The interrater agreement was slight (0.0-0.2) or fair (0.2-0.4), yet a substantial agreement was found for signal-to-noise ratio (0.64, visual model) and artifacts (0.80, baseline model).",
    "DiscussionIn this study, we presented a deep learning-based superresolution method to increase medical CBCT image quality in musculoskeletal and dental imaging domains and demonstrated how to validate the methods in several clinical domains.",
